OL,3,CNurses who contracted long Covid still
OL,4,Cwaiting for financial support
OL,6,FLisa, a former children's intensive
OL,7,Fcare nurse for 25 years, contracted
OL,8,FCovid in 2022.
OL,10,FShe worked in the adult intensive care
OL,11,Funit at various hospitals during the
OL,12,Fpandemic, and believes she contracted
OL,13,Fthe virus whilst at work.
OL,15,FLisa says she suffers from
OL,16,Fdebilitating long Covid symptoms,
OL,17,Fincluding chronic fatigue in her legs
OL,18,Fand arms, brain fog, memory loss and
OL,19,FRaynaud's phenomenon.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
